<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-51-0032 </DOCNO><TEXT>The conditions for obtaining single-crystalline nickel films with a highresistivity ratio at room temperature and at 4.2 K (up to 1000) are described.The thicknesses of the films studied fall in the range 0.7-10 {mu}m.The meanfree path length of the carriers (6-7 {mu}m) and the specularityparameter (0.05) are determined using the Fuks-Sondheimer method.</TEXT></DOC>